\cf1\b A. \b0 Most likely not. The LFO/step sequencer is not a note-based step sequencer, so it will not trigger notes with samples assigned to them.  What it can do as a step sequencer is control the pitch of a sample, and with some editing you could program a melody with it.  Another thing you could do is have the LFO move the start point of a sample, so it would scan through a long sample like a break beat or a piano loop, more or less like a slicer...\cf0\par
